devdoc.details: Version 0.3 - last updated 2022-05-19             Upgraded to include multiple studies in 1 contract

params.participant: The address of the participant that will be queried.
params.timestamp: The timestamp whose consent status needs to be known.

returns._0: The participant's consent status set at the given timestamp, or false if the participant did not update it at that moment.

addConsentToStudy(string,address).details: The function sets the mapping value that corresponds to the participant to true, whatever the initial value.         If the participant has not consented yet, or withdrew said consent, add them to the list of participants first.         This avoids 'double-spending' consent, or giving consent twice in quick succession.

params.study: The id of the study to check

params.data: The address of the new data contract address

params.new_owner: The address of the new owner

params.dataAddress: The address of the data contract

getAllStudyParticipants(string).details: The function double-checks the list of participants, ensuring that they are indeed consenting participants.

returns._0: A list of participants that have consented to the use of their data in the study.

getConsentTimestamps(string,address).details: At the time of writing (2018-12-05), Solidity does not allow returning dynamic arrays or structs.         The solution is to return a list of timestamps for a participant.         These timestamps can be used to construct a timeline by querying each timestamp.

params.participant: The address of the participant that will be queried.

returns._0: A list of timestamps when the participant updated their consent status.

getConsentTrail(string,address).details: At the time of writing (2018-12-05), Solidity does not allow returning dynamic arrays or structs.         The solution is to return a list of timestamps for a participant.         These timestamps can be used to construct a timeline by querying each timestamp.

params.participant: The address of the participant that will be queried.

returns._0: A list of timestamps when the participant updated their consent status.

getConsentingParticipants(string).details: The function double-checks the list of participants, ensuring that they are indeed consenting participants.

returns._0: A list of participants that have consented to the use of their data in the study.

params.study: The id of the study to check

returns._0: A boolean representing whether the participant has an active consent for the use of his data in the study.

withdrawConsentFromStudy(string,address).details: The function sets the mapping value that corresponds to the participant to false, whatever the initial value.         If the participant had given consent and is now withdrawing it, remove the participant from the list of consenting participants.         The deletion uses the swap technique.

params.study: The id of the study to check

devdoc.title: Study - a contract that contains consent details for a study.

GetConsentAt(string,address,uint256).notice: Get the participant's consent at a particular timestamp.         If the participant did not change their consent at this timestamp, false is returned.

addConsentToStudy(string,address).notice: The centerpiece of dynamic consent.         The sender gives consent to the use of their sample in the study.

changeLogic(address).notice: Changes the data contract address         This allows to change the data

changeOwner(address).notice: Changes the owner of this contract

constructor.notice: Create the study with its most basic details.         No consent information is collected initially.

getAllStudyParticipants(string).notice: Get the list of all participants that ever participated in the study.

getConsentTimestamps(string,address).notice: Get a list of timestamps when a participant's consent was changed.

getConsentingParticipants(string).notice: Get the list of participants that are participating in the study.

hasConsented(string,address).notice: Check whether the participant has consented to the use of their sample in this study.

withdrawConsentFromStudy(string,address).notice: The centerpiece of dynamic consent.         The sender withdraws consent to the use of their sample in the study.
